Interactive Data Analysis Using Mito

# Import the libraries
import mitosheet
mitosheet.sheet(analysis_to_replay="id-jtqwyekuoo")
Exception: The mitosheet currently only works in JupyterLab.

To see instructions on getting Mitosheet running in JupyterLab, find install instructions here: https://docs.trymito.io/getting-started/installing-mito
from mitosheet import *; register_analysis("id-jtqwyekuoo");
    
# Imported telecom.csv
import pandas as pd
telecom = pd.read_csv(r'/home/thulasiram/personal/going_deep_and_wide/GiveDirectly/data/telecom_data/telecom.csv')

# Pivoted into telecom
tmp_df = telecom[['churn', 'state']].copy()
pivot_table = tmp_df.pivot_table(
    index=['state'],
    columns=['churn'],
    values=['churn'],
    aggfunc={'churn': ['count']}
)
pivot_table = pivot_table.set_axis([flatten_column_header(col) for col in pivot_table.keys()], axis=1)
telecom_pivot = pivot_table.reset_index()

Whatever analysis we do in the Mito sheet above, the corresponding code will be generated in the Jupyter cells

Code generated by Mito for creating a Pivot table

from mitosheet import *; register_analysis("id-jtqwyekuoo");
    
# Imported telecom.csv
import pandas as pd
telecom = pd.read_csv(r'/home/thulasiram/personal/learning/data/data_analysis/telecom.csv')

# Pivoted into telecom
tmp_df = telecom[['churn', 'state']].copy()
pivot_table = tmp_df.pivot_table(
    index=['state'],
    columns=['churn'],
    values=['churn'],
    aggfunc={'churn': ['count']}
)
pivot_table = pivot_table.set_axis([flatten_column_header(col) for col in pivot_table.keys()], axis=1)
telecom_pivot = pivot_table.reset_index()

Code generated by Mito for creating a Plotly Graph

import plotly.express as px

# Filter the dataframe so that it does not crash the browser
telecom_filtered = telecom.head(1000)

# Construct the graph and style it. Further customize your graph by editing this code.
# See Plotly Documentation for help: https://plotly.com/python/plotly-express/
fig = px.bar(telecom_filtered, x='voice mail plan', y='churn')
fig.update_layout(
    title='Voice Mail Vs Churn', 
    xaxis = dict(
        title='voice mail plan', 
        showgrid=True, 
        rangeslider = dict(
            visible=True, 
            thickness=0.05
        )
    ), 
    yaxis = dict(
        title='churn', 
        showgrid=True
    ), 
    legend = dict(
        orientation='v'
    ), 
    barmode='group', 
    paper_bgcolor='#FFFFFF'
)
fig.show(renderer="iframe")

Passing a dataframe into Mito

import pandas as pd
url = 'https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/machine-learning-databases/iris/iris.data'
df = pd.read_csv(url)
# Render mitosheet with the data
mitosheet.sheet(df, analysis_to_replay="id-ujihfqivfw")
